TY  - JOUR
TI  - Some Stronger Measures of Risk Aversion in the Small and the Large with Applications
AU  - Ross, Stephen A.
AB  - [This paper argues that the traditional Arrow-Pratt measures of risk aversion are generally too weak for making comparisons between risky situations. A new stronger ordering is proposed, and it is applied to some canonical problems in insurance and finance, for which the Arrow-Pratt measures give ambiguous results.]
